(312, 'If you open dashboard view file , you will see there are conditional statment \r\n\r\n```\r\n@if(Auth::check() && Auth::user()->group_id == 1)\r\n\r\n\r\n@endif \r\n```\r\nthis mean only superadmin can access the widget/menu link \r\n\r\nso what if you want to make other dashboard ?\r\n\r\nJust create new additional statement\r\n\r\n ```\r\n@if(Auth::check() && Auth::user()->group_id == 1)\r\n // Code view for superadmin\r\n@else\r\n// Code view for non superadmin\r\n@endif \r\n```', 1, '2015-08-27 16:41:30', 184),
(307, 'you can create your own function for select combo . here example function in your controller\r\n```\r\n	function getMyselectcustom( Request $request)\r\n	{\r\n		$items = array();\r\n		$rows =  \\DB::select( "SELECT * FROM your table ORDER BY field DESC ");\r\n		foreach($rows as $row) \r\n		{\r\n			\r\n			$items[] = array(''key'' , $row->fieldname); 	\r\n\r\n		}\r\n		return json_encode($items); \r\n\r\n	}\r\n```\r\nNext , just point your javascript for comboselect to new controller function\r\n\r\n```\r\n $("#fieldID").jCombo("{{ URL::to(''mymodule/myselectcustom'') }}",\r\n        {  selected_value : ''{{ $row["fieldID"] }}'' });\r\n```', 1, '2015-08-27 16:31:58', 197),
