(163, 'Create a detailed audit trail for tables CRUD transactions using the "triggers" tool in phpmyadmin', NULL, 'Suppose we created a table "employees" with the following structure\r\n\r\n`employeeNumber` int(11) NOT NULL, (AI, PK)\r\n  `lastName` varchar(50) NOT NULL,\r\n  `firstName` varchar(50) NOT NULL,\r\n  `extension` varchar(10) NOT NULL,\r\n  `email` varchar(100) NOT NULL,\r\n  `reportsTo` int(11) DEFAULT NULL,\r\n  `jobTitle` varchar(50) NOT NULL,\r\n  `foto` varchar(100) DEFAULT NULL\r\n\r\nto create a full audit log we can use phpmyadmin triggers\r\nthe following is one example for logging delete transactions\r\n1-copy table "employees" to a new table "employees_audit", add new AI column and set as primary key instead of Employeesnumber. Also add a timestamp filed\r\n2-create a new trigger in table "employees" = "employee_audit_before_delete"\r\n3-fill the following in the pop up windows: table="employees", time="before", event="delete", definer="root@localhost"\r\n4-write the following:\r\nINSERT INTO employees_audit\r\n   (employeeNumber,lastName,firstName,extension,email,reportsTo,jobTitle,foto)\r\n        VALUES\r\n   (OLD.employeeNumber,OLD.lastName,OLD.firstName,OLD.extension,OLD.email,OLD.reportsTo,OLD.jobTitle,OLD.foto)\r\n', 2, '2015-07-28 12:18:24', 0, 1502, '0'),
