(276, 'How can i create new options for the front end and backend', NULL, 'What i am trying to add is a < FORM SELECT > for theme layout template  and i would like to make the same thing for the admin area both theme select and template layout file select.\r\n\r\n_EXAMPLE_\r\n#### Frontend Theme\r\n\r\n- Theme SELECT: <br>\r\n   **frontend theme:**<br>\r\n   - sximo<br>\r\n      **theme layout template:**<br>\r\n      - full-layout\r\n      - no-sidebar\r\n      - basic-page\r\n   - other<br>\r\n      **theme layout template:**<br>\r\n      - full-layout\r\n      - no-sidebar\r\n      - basic-page\r\n\r\n#### Admin Theme\r\n\r\n- Admin Theme SELECT: <br>\r\n     **admin theme:**<br>\r\n   - customAdmin\r\n   - adminLte <br>\r\n      **admin template layout:**<br>\r\n      - full-layout\r\n      - no-sidebar\r\n      - basic-page<br>\r\n   - sximoAdmin<br>\r\n      **admin template layout:**<br>\r\n      - full-layout\r\n      - no-sidebar\r\n      - basic-page<br>\r\n   - otherAdmin<br>\r\n      **admin template layout:**<br>\r\n      - full-layout\r\n      - no-sidebar\r\n      - basic-page<br>', 16, '2015-11-26 00:30:15', 10, 538, '0'),
(277, 'Can''t get installation running due to __DIR__ . ', NULL, 'I just downloaded Sximo 5 and went through the download steps\r\n\r\nBut the I can''t get to the login screen, nothing but a blank\r\n\r\nThen I see that your entire application is using __DIR__  to provide the directory path\r\nso while I am trying to run this application in the localhost environment all of file dependencies are looking like this example\r\n\r\n C:\\Bitnami\\wampstack-5.4.38-0\\apache2\\htdocs\\laravelapp\\public/../bootstrap/autoload.php../setting.php \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nso the hard file location is incompatible with all of the files and folders in the Sximo application marked like this /../bootstrap/autoload.php\r\n\r\nI experimented with backtracking through the files and providing the localhost friendly urls but there are just too many to waste my time\r\n\r\nI see this in server.php\r\n\r\n``` \r\n$uri = urldecode(\r\n    parse_url($_SERVER[''REQUEST_URI''], PHP_URL_PATH)\r\n);\r\n\r\n// This file allows us to emulate Apache''s "mod_rewrite" functionality from the\r\n// built-in PHP web server. This provides a convenient way to test a Laravel\r\n// application without having installed a "real" web server software here.\r\nif ($uri !== ''/'' and file_exists(__DIR__.''/public''.$uri)) {\r\n    return false;\r\n}\r\n\r\nrequire_once __DIR__.''/public/index.php'';\r\n``` \r\nSome explanation is missing in your installation documents that I would like to get a fix for.\r\n\r\nThank you!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', 3, '2015-11-26 23:47:56', 0, 2091, '0'),
(278, ' 500 internal server error', NULL, 'Hi, i need some help. When i try to create new entry or edit existing one i receive 500 internal server error, and ajax loader keeps spinning. This happens only with ajax enabled. When in native mode it works fine. Any clue on what could be causing this problem. Thx..', 17, '2015-12-01 08:38:48', 0, 2084, '0'),
(279, '"Apply Changes / Save" Duplicates New Record', NULL, 'We found that Edit > Save creates duplicated record.\r\nAny reason for this? please kindly help\r\n\r\nFound in the codes:\r\nIn the function postSave in XXXController generated by Code Builder,\r\nthe code "insertRow" always called, thus creates new record for every Save.\r\n\r\n', 3, '2015-12-02 03:36:12', 1, 1525, '0'),
(280, 'Search box in top of each column', NULL, 'Hi, \r\n\r\nI''m implementing sximo and already have some modules working. \r\n\r\nIn your demos and tutorial when a new module is created in the top of each column you get a search box. I''m trying to make the same but in my case I can''t implement search for each column.\r\n\r\nThanks', 17, '2015-12-04 10:39:47', 5, 2138, '0'),
(282, 'More than 1 entry_by user?', NULL, 'Good day,\r\n\r\nI am using Sximo for my own product and like it a lot! \r\n\r\nI just need some help with making a table row available for multiple entry_by''s. So both my customer as my merchant can see their own orders. \r\n\r\nHow can i insert this new functionality? \r\n\r\nHope to hear from you! \r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\n\r\nTom', 2, '2015-12-08 13:04:31', 4, 524, '0'),
